s. When Thais arrived in Los Angeles, they reinvented and repackaged Thai food in various ways to meet the rising popularity of the cuisine in urban and suburban spaces. Padoongpatt opens up the history and politics of Thai food for the first time, all while demonstrating how race emerges in seemingly mundane and unexpected places.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aCooking, Thai. 0aThais - California - Los Angeles - Social life and customs. 0aThaiszCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial conditions. 0aThaiszCaliforniazLos AngelesxSocial life and customs. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966925423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520966925.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles